Gunmen suspected to be bandits have attacked Gidan train station along the Abuja-Kaduna rail track. It was gathered that the terrorists planted IEDs on the tracks, forcing a train heading to Abuja from Kaduna to stop. SaharaReporters Media This is the second attack within 24 hours along the same axis. SaharaReporters had reported how terrorists on Monday night bombed the Abuja-Kaduna rail tracks and attacked a train filled with passengers.  PHOTONEWS: Scores Killed, Many Injured As Terrorists Bomb Abuja-Kaduna Train Conveying Over 900 Passengers In Latest Of Train Attacks In Nigeria pic.twitter.com/nP31RIWHsu  Eight persons have been confirmed dead in the attack with many kidnapped.Â One of the survivors of the train attack told SaharaReporters on Tuesday that the terrorists told them that the Nigerian government should expect more attacks as they had just started. This comes a few hours after another set of terrorists killed six soldiers from Zuma barracks, Suleja, Niger State. 